-- Abengoa Gets $125 Million Investment for U.S. Solar Project
-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 2012-04-20T10:41:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-20/abengoa-gets-125-million-investment-for-u-s-solar-project.html
Abengoa SA (ABG)  said  Banco Santander SA (SAN) 
will invest $125 million in a $2 billion U.S. solar thermal
project that may be the largest of its kind in the world when it
starts working in 2013.  The Spanish energy developer made a statement about the
project by e-mail today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marc Roca in London at 
